  "local_port": 42702,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What advice do you have for a seventeen year old who is pretty confused in life?",
  "response": "It\u2019s completely normal to feel confused at seventeen\u2014you\u2019re navigating a time of immense change, self-discovery, and decision-making. Here\u2019s some advice to help you feel more grounded and empowered:\n\n### 1. **Embrace the Uncertainty**\n   - It\u2019s okay not to have everything figured out. Life is a journey, and you\u2019re still exploring who you are and what you want. Give yourself permission to be unsure.\n\n### 2. **Focus on Self-Discovery**\n   - Experiment with different interests, hobbies, and activities. Try new things without worrying about whether they\u2019ll define your future. This is the time to explore and learn about yourself.\n   - Reflect on what makes you happy, what drains your energy, and what you\u2019re naturally curious about.\n\n### 3. **Set Small, Achievable Goals**\n   - Instead of overwhelming yourself with big, long-term plans, focus on small steps. What can you do today or this week that aligns with your values or interests?\n   - Celebrate small wins\u2014they build confidence and momentum.\n\n### 4. **Seek Guidance, but Trust Yourself**\n   - Talk to trusted adults, mentors, or friends for advice, but remember that your path is unique. You don\u2019t have to follow someone else\u2019s blueprint for success.\n   - Trust your instincts\u2014you know yourself better than anyone else.\n\n### 5. **Don\u2019t Compare Yourself to Others**\n   - Everyone\u2019s journey is different. Social media and peer pressure can make it seem like others have it all figured out, but that\u2019s rarely the case. Focus on your own progress.\n\n### 6. **Take Care of Your Mental and Physical Health**\n   - Prioritize your well-being. Exercise, eat well, sleep enough, and practice mindfulness or relaxation techniques. Mental health is just as important as physical health.\n\n### 7. **Remember, It\u2019s Okay to Change Your Mind**\n   - Your interests, goals, and dreams may shift over time, and that\u2019s normal. Flexibility and adaptability are key to navigating life\u2019s ups and downs.\n\n### 8. **Build Healthy Habits**\n   - Develop habits that will serve you well in the long run, like reading, journaling, saving money, or learning new skills. These small investments in yourself will pay off over time.\n\n### 9. **Don\u2019t Rush**\n   - There\u2019s no deadline for figuring things out. Take your time to explore, make mistakes, and grow. Life isn\u2019t a race\u2014it\u2019s about finding meaning and joy along the way.\n\n### 10. **Be Kind to Yourself**\n   - Treat yourself with the same compassion and understanding you\u2019d offer a friend. Mistakes and setbacks are part of learning\u2014they don\u2019t define your worth or future.\n\n### 11. **Look for Opportunities to Learn**\n   - Whether it\u2019s through school, work, volunteering, or personal projects, seek out experiences that challenge and inspire you. Every experience teaches you something valuable.\n\n### 12. **Remember, You\u2019re Not Alone**\n   - Everyone feels lost or confused at some point, even if they don\u2019t show it. Reach out to friends, family, or a counselor if you need support. You don\u2019t have to figure it all out on your own.\n\n### 13. **Keep an Open Mind**\n   - Life rarely goes exactly as planned, and that\u2019s okay. Stay open to unexpected opportunities and paths\u2014they might lead you somewhere amazing.\n\n### 14. **Focus on What You Can Control**\n   - While many things in life are uncertain, you can control your attitude, effort, and how you treat others. Focus on these areas to build a sense of purpose and direction.\n\n### 15. **Believe in Your Potential**\n   - You\u2019re capable of more than you realize. Even if things feel overwhelming now, trust that you have the strength and resilience to navigate whatever comes your way.\n\nRemember, confusion is often a sign of growth\u2014it means you\u2019re questioning, exploring, and striving for something more. Take it one step at a time, and know that you\u2019re exactly where you need to be right now. You\u2019ve got this! \ud83c\udf1f",
  "temperature": 1.0,
